OL,3,CStalking victims to be given more
OL,4,Cprotection under new measures
OL,6,FIf someone is acquitted, courts will
OL,7,Fstill have the power to apply
OL,8,Fprotection orders directly if there is
OL,9,Fenough evidence to suggest that the
OL,10,Fperson is still a risk to someone, the
OL,11,FHome Office added.
OL,13,FThe government has also promised a
OL,14,Freview of stalking legislation to
OL,15,Fdetermine whether the law could be
OL,16,Fchanged to support police to better
OL,17,Fidentify stalking and arrest offenders.
